{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17598345","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17598345"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:36:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:36:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15465"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15465","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15465"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.48,0.29,0,0.13,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8156"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64322"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8156"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15465"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49754"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6812"},{"type":"tags","id":"8109"},{"type":"tags","id":"9906"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19760"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19763"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64322","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64322"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPulmonary shunting occurs when deoxygenated blood bypasses ventilated alveoli and enters the systemic circulation without being oxygenated.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following conditions most commonly causes pulmonary shunting?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alveolar collapse","Pulmonary embolism","Haemorrhagic shock","Emphysema","Pneumothorax"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn pulmonary shunting, blood flows through areas of lung that are not being ventilated, resulting in poor oxygenation of blood. \u003Cstrong\u003EAlveolar collapse\u003C/strong\u003E (atelectasis) is a common cause of shunting because blood continues to flow through collapsed alveoli that cannot participate in gas exchange.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPulmonary embolism\u003C/strong\u003E causes dead space ventilation rather than shunting, as alveoli are ventilated but not perfused. \u003Cstrong\u003EHaemorrhagic shock\u003C/strong\u003E would lead to reduced perfusion through the lungs but would not affect ventilation, therefore similarly creating increased alveolar dead space rather than a shunt. \u003Cstrong\u003EEmphysema\u003C/strong\u003E is another cause of increased dead space through destruction of alveolar walls. A \u003Cstrong\u003Epneumothorax\u003C/strong\u003E results in collapse of lung tissue but affects both ventilation and perfusion of the affected area and is a not a specific cause of shunt.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ventilation-perfusion mismatch occurs when blood flows through unventilated alveoli (shunt) or when ventilated alveoli receive no blood flow (dead space)","Alveolar collapse (atelectasis) is a common cause of pulmonary shunting","Pulmonary shunting leads to hypoxaemia that does not improve with supplemental oxygen"],"references":["Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Spinelli E, Mauri T. Alveolar Collapse as a Threat to Mechanically Ventilated Lungs. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 2024 Jun 15;209(12):1418-1420. doi: 10.1164/rccm.202402-0326ED. PMID: 38546274; PMCID: PMC11208958.","Lutz D, Gazdhar A, Lopez-Rodriguez E, Ruppert C, Mahavadi P, G\u00fcnther A, Klepetko W, Bates JH, Smith B, Geiser T, Ochs M, Knudsen L. Alveolar derecruitment and collapse induration as crucial mechanisms in lung injury and fibrosis. Am J Respir Cell Mol Biol. 2015 Feb;52(2):232-43. doi: 10.1165/rcmb.2014-0078OC. PMID: 25033427."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49754"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15465"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49754"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-23T12:20:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-23T12:22:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8156"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64322"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},